<HTMLTableRowElementVAlign>
<summary>
<div class="IMPORTANT"><h5>IMPORTANT</h5> <strong>Deprecated</strong></div> The <strong><c>vAlign</c></strong> property of the <see cref="HTMLTableRowElement"/> interface is a string indicating how to vertically align text in a {{htmlelement("tr")}} table row. Individual cells can override it.
</summary>
<remarks>
<blockquote class="NOTE"><h5>NOTE</h5><para>This property is deprecated. Use the CSS <see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/vertical-align">vertical-align</see> property to horizontally align text in a row instead.</para></blockquote>
<para>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/vertical-align">vertical-align</see><br/>-<see href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Learn_web_development/Core/Styling_basics/Tables">Learn: Styling tables</see><br/></para>
<para><seealso href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/HTMLTableRowElement/vAlign"> <em>See also on MDN</em> </seealso></para>
</remarks>
<value>The possible values are: <c>&amp;quot;top&amp;quot;</c>, <c>&amp;quot;middle&amp;quot;</c>, <c>&amp;quot;bottom&amp;quot;</c>, or <c>&amp;quot;baseline&amp;quot;</c></value>
</HTMLTableRowElementVAlign>
